{"sha": "f0f04e1dffea609cb74ac0b488385401ed7e15a3", "node_id": "C_kwDOANBUbNoAKGYwZjA0ZTFkZmZlYTYwOWNiNzRhYzBiNDg4Mzg1NDAxZWQ3ZTE1YTM", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Jonathan Wakely", "email": "jwakely@redhat.com", "date": "2022-08-23T23:10:59Z"}, "committer": {"name": "Jonathan Wakely", "email": "jwakely@redhat.com", "date": "2022-08-24T11:27:51Z"}, "message": "libstdc++: Add check for LWG 3741 problem case\n\nThis LWG issue was closed as NAD, as it was just a bug in an\nimplementation, not a defect in the standard. Libstdc++ never had that\nbug and always worked for the problem case. Add a test to ensure we\ndon't regress.\n\nThe problem occurs when abs is implemented using a ternary expression:\n\n return d >= d.zero() ? d : -d;\n\nIf decltype(-d) is not the same as decltype(d) then this is ambiguous,\nbecause each type can be converted to the other, so there is no common\ntype.\n\nlibstdc++-v3/ChangeLog:\n\n\t* testsuite/20_util/duration_cast/rounding.cc: Check abs with\n\tnon-reduced duration.", "tree": {"sha": "c0b52c14c2878b85dc0946baf03645d2bd3cdb99", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/git/trees/c0b52c14c2878b85dc0946baf03645d2bd3cdb99"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/git/commits/f0f04e1dffea609cb74ac0b488385401ed7e15a3", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commits/f0f04e1dffea609cb74ac0b488385401ed7e15a3", "html_url": "https://github.com/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commit/f0f04e1dffea609cb74ac0b488385401ed7e15a3", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commits/f0f04e1dffea609cb74ac0b488385401ed7e15a3/comments", "author": {"login": "jwakely", "id": 1254480, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEyNTQ0ODA=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1254480?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jwakely", "html_url": "https://github.com/jwakely", "followers_url"